data.name: checkBox_pages_can_be_closed.ToolTip
data.value: If set, end user can close the tab control using the tabpage on the layout controls. Closing control just hide it from user, not dispose it. If this option is set, it is recommended to include the dynamic menu item that allows to hide and show tabcontrols under the name "Tabs" unless you don't want the end user to change tabs visibilty.

data.name: linkLabel2.ToolTip
data.value: Reset colors for menus and toolbars only

data.name: linkLabel1.ToolTip
data.value: Reset colors for tab pages only

data.name: checkBox_tabs_can_be_reordered.ToolTip
data.value: If set, end user can change the location of the tab control in the tabpages control. Disable this if you don't want the end user to be able to change the layout of the tabs in your application.

data.name: checkBox_pages_can_be_dragged.Text
data.value: Tab pages can be &draged and droped.

data.name: checkBox_pages_can_be_dragged.ToolTip
data.value:
IMPORTANT !! This is a very important choise to take.
If this is set, user will be able to change the layout of the tabpages with drag-and-drop, thus, your application layout become changable.
If this is NOT set, user won't be able to change the layout of the tabpages with drag-and-drop, thus, your application layout become fixed and changable.
